A number of popular musicians, including Zonke, Thandiswa Mazwai and Caiphus Semenya will headline this year’s Mzansi Fela Festival. JOHANNESBURG - Mzansi Fela Festival returns for the 12th consecutive year with explosive musical acts and thought-provoking art. A number of popular musicians, including Zonke, Thandiswa Mazwai and Caiphus Semenya will headline this year’s Mzansi Fela Festival. READ:John Lennon's round sunglasses to be sold at auction The three-week festival which begins on December 1, 2019 and ends December 22, 2019, includes poetry, productions, exhibitions and dancing. The festival includes socially conscious dialogues on World Aids Day and 16 days of activism through lectures and various art forms.